data.after: Create a function that invokes once it's called n or more times.
data.allKeys: Retrieve all the names of object's own and inherited properties.
data.before: Create a function that invokes less than n times.
data.bind: Create a function bound to a given object.
data.capitalize: Convert the first character to upper case and the remaining to lower case.
data.cookie: Simple api for handling browser cookies.
data.createAssigner: Used to create extend, extendOwn and defaults.
data.defaults: Fill in undefined properties in object with the first value present in the following list of defaults objects.
data.each: Iterates over elements of collection and invokes iteratee for each element.
data.endWith: Check if string ends with the given target string.
data.escape: Escapes a string for insertion into HTML, replacing &, <, >, ", `, and ' characters.
data.every: Check if predicate return truthy for all elements.
data.extend: Copy all of the properties in the source objects over to the destination object.
data.extendOwn: Like extend, but only copies own properties over to the destination object.
data.extractBlockCmts: Extract block comments from source code.
data.filter: Iterates over elements of collection, returning an array of all the values that pass a truth test.
data.findKey: Return the key where the predicate truth test passes or undefined.
data.has: Checks if key is a direct property.
data.idxOf: Get the index at which the first occurrence of value.
data.inherits: Inherit the prototype methods from one constructor into another.
data.invert: Create an object composed of the inverted keys and values of object.
data.isArgs: Check if value is classified as an arguments object.
data.isArr: Check if value is an `Array` object.
data.isBool: Check if value is a boolean primitive.
data.isDate: Check if value is classified as a Date object.
data.isEl: Check if value is a DOM element.
data.isEmpty: Check if value is an empty object or array.
data.isErr: Check if value is an error.
data.isFinite: Check if value is a finite primitive number.
data.isFn: Check if value is a function.
data.isInt: Checks if value is classified as a Integer.
data.isMatch: Check if keys and values in src are contained in obj.
data.isMobile: Check whether client is using a mobile browser using ua.
data.isNaN: Check if value is an NaN.
data.isNum: Checks if value is classified as a Number primitive or object.
data.isObj: Check if value is the language type of Object.
data.isPrimitive: Check if value is string, number, boolean or null.
data.isRegExp: Check if value is a regular expression.
data.isRelative: Check if path appears to be relative.
data.isStr: Check if value is a string primitive.
data.keys: Create an array of the own enumerable property names of object.
data.last: Get the last element of array.
data.loadJs: Inject script tag into page with given src value.
data.lpad: Pad string on the left side if it's shorter than length.
data.ltrim: Remove chars or white-spaces from beginning of string.
data.map: Create an array of values by running each element in collection through iteratee.
data.max: Get maximum value of given numbers.
data.min: Get minimum value of given numbers.
data.now: Gets the number of milliseconds that have elapsed since the Unix epoch.
data.once: Create a function that invokes once.
data.pad: Pad string on the left and right sides if it's shorter than length.
data.partial: Partially apply a function by filling in given arguments.
data.random: Produces a random number between min and max(inclusive).
data.restArgs: This accumulates the arguments passed into an array, after a given index.
data.root: Root object reference, `global` in nodeJs, `window` in browser.
data.rpad: Pad string on the right side if it's shorter than length.
data.rtrim: Remove chars or white-spaces from end of string.
data.size: Get size of object, length of array like object or the number of keys.
data.startWith: Check if string starts with the given target string.
data.stripColor: Strip ansi characters from a string.
data.trim: Remove chars or white-spaces from beginning end of string.
data.unescape: Convert HTML entities back, the inverse of escape.
data.unique: Create duplicate-free version of an array.
data.values: Creates an array of the own enumerable property values of object.
data.wrap: Wrap the function inside a wrapper function, passing it as the first argument.
